4$ in the mixing-length parameter around the solar-calibrated value causes\nin last 5% of the MS an uncertainty from -0.09 to +0.15. A complete neglect of\ndiffusion in the stellar evolution computations produces a $1 \\sigma$\nuncertainty of $\\pm 0.08$ in the last 5% of the MS, while $\\beta$ is\npractically unconstrained in the first 80% of the MS. Overall, the calibration\nappears poorly reliable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Jan 2016 13:45:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-17"}
